1.1.3 Normalization and filtering (Demo)

# Read mRNA expression data
all_brca_RNA <- readRDS(url("https://wd.cri.uic.edu/machine_learning/brca_RNA_TPM.rds"))

# Apply log2(x + 1) normalization function to TPM data
all_brca_RNA.log2 <- as.data.frame(lapply(all_brca_RNA[,4:ncol(all_brca_RNA)],
                                          FUN = function(x) {log2(x + 1)}))
all_brca_RNA.log2 <- cbind(all_brca_RNA[,1:3], all_brca_RNA.log2)
colnames(all_brca_RNA.log2) <- colnames(all_brca_RNA)

# Keep only those genes with at least 30% of samples with log2(TPM) > 0.
keep <- (rowSums(
  all_brca_RNA.log2[,4:ncol(all_brca_RNA.log2)] > 0) 
  >= ncol(all_brca_RNA.log2[,4:ncol(all_brca_RNA.log2)])*0.3)
all_brca_RNA.log2.filtered <- all_brca_RNA.log2[keep,]

1.1.4 Make a balanced dataset (Demo)

library(tidyverse)

# Read clinical data
brca_cli <- readRDS(url("https://wd.cri.uic.edu/machine_learning/brca_clinical.rds"))

# Get samples of ductal and lobular types of breast cancer
brca_cli.ductal <- brca_cli[
  brca_cli$CANCER_TYPE_DETAILED=="Breast Invasive Ductal Carcinoma",]
brca_cli.lobular <- brca_cli[
  brca_cli$CANCER_TYPE_DETAILED=="Breast Invasive Lobular Carcinoma",]
brca_cli.ductal <- brca_cli.ductal[!is.na(brca_cli.ductal$sampleId),]
brca_cli.lobular <- brca_cli.lobular[!is.na(brca_cli.lobular$sampleId),]
num_ductal <- nrow(brca_cli.ductal)
num_lobular <- nrow(brca_cli.lobular)

# Since number of lobular samples is < than ductal, select a subset of ductal samples
set.seed(123)
ductal.samples <- sample(brca_cli.ductal$sampleId, num_lobular, replace = F)
ductal.exp <- all_brca_RNA.log2.filtered[,ductal.samples]
lobular.samples <- brca_cli.lobular$sampleId
lobular.exp <- all_brca_RNA.log2.filtered[,lobular.samples]
rownames(ductal.exp) <- all_brca_RNA.log2.filtered$hugoGeneSymbol
rownames(lobular.exp) <- all_brca_RNA.log2.filtered$hugoGeneSymbol

# Combine ductal and lobular expression datasets and convert to matrix
ductal.mat   <- as.matrix(ductal.exp)
lobular.mat  <- as.matrix(lobular.exp)
expr_combined <- cbind(ductal.mat, lobular.mat)
n_ductal  <- ncol(ductal.mat)
n_lobular <- ncol(lobular.mat)
labels <- c(rep("Ductal", n_ductal), rep("Lobular", n_lobular))
table(labels)
## labels
##  Ductal Lobular 
##     206     206
# Build data.frame for modeling: samples x genes
df <- as.data.frame(t(expr_combined))  # rows = samples, cols = genes
df <- tibble::rownames_to_column(df, var = "sample_id")
df$class <- factor(labels, levels = c("Ductal","Lobular"))
colnames(df) <- gsub("-","_",colnames(df)) # Fix gene names so there aren't errors

1.1.5 Split into training and testing cohorts

library(tidyverse)
library(caret)

# Read samples x genes data frame for modeling
df <- readRDS(url("https://wd.cri.uic.edu/machine_learning/ML_df.rds"))

library(caret)
set.seed(123)
train_idx <- createDataPartition(df$class, p = 0.7, list = FALSE)
train_df  <- df[train_idx, ]
test_df   <- df[-train_idx, ]

# For convenience, create X and y
x_train <- train_df %>% select(-sample_id, -class)
y_train <- train_df$class
x_test  <- test_df  %>% select(-sample_id, -class)
y_test  <- test_df$class

1.2 Feature selection

1.2.1 Variance filtering of features

# Compute variance per gene
gene_vars <- apply(x_train, 2, var)

# Keep top 500 variable genes (adjust as needed)
df_features <- train_df %>% select(-sample_id)
top_var_genes <- names(sort(gene_vars, decreasing = TRUE))[1:500]
df_var_filtered <- df_features[, c(top_var_genes, "class")]

1.2.2 T-test filtering of features

# T-test to rank remaining features
ttest_ranks <- apply(x_train, 2, function(g) {
  t.test(g ~ y_train)$statistic
})
ttest_ranks <- sort(abs(ttest_ranks), decreasing = TRUE)

# Pick the top 100 genes
df_features <- train_df %>% select(-sample_id)
top_ttest_genes <- names(ttest_ranks)[1:100]
df_ttest_filtered <- df_features[, c(top_ttest_genes, "class")]

1.3 Logistic regression model with RFE

library(caret)
library(ggplot2)

# RFE setup
rfe_ctrl <- rfeControl(functions = lrFuncs, 
                   method = "cv", # cross validation
                   number = 10) # number of folds

# Number of features to be retained in the updated model
sizes <- c(5, 10, 15, 20, 25, 30, 35, 40, 45, 50)

# Run RFE
set.seed(123)
rfe_results <- rfe(
  x = df_ttest_filtered %>% select(-class),
  y = df_ttest_filtered$class,
  sizes = sizes,
  rfeControl = rfe_ctrl
)

print(rfe_results)

1.4.4 Calculate F1 statistics on test set

library(caret)
library(MLmetrics)

# Subset training and testing data to the selected features
Xtr <- x_train[, best_rfe_feats_all]
Xte  <- x_test[,  best_rfe_feats_all]

# Make training control function
lr_ctrl_F1 <- trainControl(
  method = "cv",
  number = 10,
  classProbs = TRUE,
  savePredictions = "final", 
  summaryFunction = function(data, lev = NULL, model = NULL) {
    f1 <- F1_Score(y_pred = data$pred, y_true = data$obs, positive = lev[2])
    c(F1 = f1)
    }
  )

# Train logistic regression with 10-fold CV
set.seed(123)
lr_model2 <- train(
  x = Xtr,
  y = y_train,
  method = "glm",
  family = "binomial",
  metric = "F1",
  trControl = lr_ctrl_F1
)

1.5 Test cohort and cross-validation with LR, cofusion matrix, ROC/AUC

library(caret)
library(ggplot2)
library(pROC)

# Get training and testing data
Xtr <- readRDS(url("https://wd.cri.uic.edu/machine_learning/Xtr.rds"))
Xte <- readRDS(url("https://wd.cri.uic.edu/machine_learning/Xte.rds"))
y_train <- readRDS(url("https://wd.cri.uic.edu/machine_learning/y_train.rds"))
y_test <- readRDS(url("https://wd.cri.uic.edu/machine_learning/y_test.rds"))

# Train a logistic model using cross-validation
# Compare accuracy and predictions of CV and test set

# Define cross-validation
lr_ctrl <- trainControl(
  method = "cv",
  number = 10,              # 10-fold CV
  classProbs = TRUE,
  summaryFunction = twoClassSummary, # Report ROC, Sensitivity, and Specificity
  savePredictions = "final"  # keep CV predictions
)

set.seed(123)
# Train logistic regression
lr_model <- train(
  x = Xtr,
  y = y_train,
  method = "glm",
  family = "binomial",
  trControl = lr_ctrl,
  metric = "Accuracy"
)
lr_model # CV results summary

2 Afternoon

2.1 Train an SVM model using the same predictors

library(caret)
library(kernlab)

# Train SVM with caret (automatically tunes cost and sigma for linear kernel)
svm_ctrl <- trainControl(
  method = "cv",   # cross-validation
  number = 10,     # 10-fold CV
  classProbs = TRUE,
  summaryFunction = twoClassSummary, # Report ROC, Sensitivity, and Specificity
  savePredictions = "final"  # keep CV predictions
)

set.seed(123)
svm_model <- train(
  y_train ~ .,
  data = data.frame(y_train, Xtr),
  method = "svmLinear",
  trControl = svm_ctrl,
  metric = "Accuracy"   # optimize by accuracy
)

# Test predictions
svm_probs <- predict(svm_model, newdata = Xte, type = "prob")
head(svm_probs[2])
svm_preds <- predict(svm_model, newdata = Xte)
head(svm_preds)
## [1] Ductal  Ductal  Ductal  Ductal  Ductal  Lobular
## Levels: Ductal Lobular
table(svm_preds)
## svm_preds

library(caret)

# Train xgb model with caret

  method = "cv",
  number = 10,
  classProbs = TRUE,
  summaryFunction = twoClassSummary,
  savePredictions = "final",
  verboseIter = FALSE
  )

set.seed(123)
xgb_model <- train(
  y_train ~ ., 
  data = data.frame(y_train, Xtr),
  method = "xgbTree",
  trControl = xgb_ctrl,
  metric = "Accuracy",
  tuneGrid = expand.grid(
    nrounds = c(50, 100),    # The total number of trees built sequentially
    max_depth = c(2, 3, 4), # maximum depth of a tree
    eta = c(0.05, 0.1, 0.3), # learning rate, shrinkage
    gamma = 0, # pruning parameter: 0 -> tree keeps splitting as long as it reduces error
    colsample_bytree = 1, # Fraction of features randomly chosen to build each tree
    min_child_weight = 1, # Controls the minimum amount of data needed in a leaf node
    subsample = 1 # Fraction of training data sampled for growing each tree
  ),
  verbosity = 0     # hides xgboost internal warnings
)

# Predict on test set
xgb_probs <- predict(xgb_model, newdata = Xte, type = "prob")
head(xgb_probs[2])

2.4 Linear regression model for Age

library(glmnet)
library(ggplot2)

# Get normalized expression data and clinical data
all_brca_RNA.log2 <- readRDS(url(
  "https://wd.cri.uic.edu/machine_learning/all_brca_RNA.log2.rds"))
brca_cli <- readRDS(url("https://wd.cri.uic.edu/machine_learning/brca_clinical.rds"))

# Create dataset with all breast cancer expression data
brca.exp <- all_brca_RNA.log2[,c(4:ncol(all_brca_RNA.log2))]
rownames(brca.exp) <- all_brca_RNA.log2$hugoGeneSymbol
rownames(brca.exp) <- gsub("-","_",rownames(brca.exp))
brca.keep <- (rowSums(brca.exp > 0) >= ncol(brca.exp)*0.3)
brca.exp.filtered <- brca.exp[brca.keep,]
brca.df <- as.data.frame(t(brca.exp.filtered))  # rows = samples, cols = genes

# Do variance filtering and keep top 500
brca.gene_vars <- apply(brca.df, 2, var)
brca.top_var_genes <- names(sort(brca.gene_vars, decreasing = TRUE))[1:500]
brca.df.var_filt <- brca.df[, brca.top_var_genes]

# Get all sample where there is an Age value
keep <- !is.na(brca_cli$AGE)
brca.age.df <- brca.df.var_filt[keep, ]

# Do a Ridge linear regression with CV
x <- as.matrix(brca.age.df)
y <- as.numeric(brca_cli$AGE[keep])
set.seed(123)
cvfit <- cv.glmnet(x, y,
                   family = "gaussian", # regression with MSE
                   alpha = 0,   # Ridge,
                   nfolds = 5)  # 5-fold CV
best_lambda <- cvfit$lambda.min

lin_model <- glmnet(x, y, alpha = 0, lambda = best_lambda)

# Predictions
preds_lin <- predict(lin_model, newx = x)

# Performance (R², RMSE)
r2_lin <- cor(preds_lin, y)^2
rmse_lin <- sqrt(mean((preds_lin - y)^2))

# Make a plot of regression=
df_pred <- data.frame(
  Observed = y,
  Predicted = as.numeric(preds_lin)
)

# Scatter plot with 1:1 line
metrics_text <- paste0("R² = ", round(r2_lin, 3), 
                       "\nRMSE = ", round(rmse_lin, 2))

ggplot(df_pred, aes(x = Observed, y = Predicted)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.6, color = "steelblue") +
  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, color = "red", linetype = "dashed") +
  annotate("text", 
           x = 25, 
           y = 60, 
           label = metrics_text, 
           hjust = 0, size = 4) +
  labs(
    title = "Ridge Regression: Predicted vs Observed Age",
    x = "Observed Age",
    y = "Predicted Age"
  ) +
  theme_classic()

2.5 Predict survival probability

library(glmnet)
library(survival)
library(survcomp)
library(survminer)
library(doParallel)

# Get clinical data and variance filtered data
brca_cli <- readRDS(url("https://wd.cri.uic.edu/machine_learning/brca_clinical.rds"))
brca.df.var_filt <- readRDS(url(
  "https://wd.cri.uic.edu/machine_learning/brca.df.var_filt.rds"))

# Get samples with complete cases of DFS_MONTHS and DFS_STATUS from the clinical data
keep <- complete.cases(brca_cli$DFS_MONTHS, 
                       brca_cli$DFS_STATUS) & brca_cli$DFS_MONTHS >= 0
DFS_MONTHS_clean <- brca_cli$DFS_MONTHS[keep]
DFS_STATUS_clean <- brca_cli$DFS_STATUS[keep]
brca.clean.df <- brca.df.var_filt[keep, ]

# Adjust 0 times
DFS_MONTHS_clean[DFS_MONTHS_clean == 0 & 
                   DFS_STATUS_clean == "1:Recurred/Progressed"] <- 0.001

# Drop 0-month censored patients
keep2 <- !(DFS_MONTHS_clean == 0 & DFS_STATUS_clean == "0:DiseaseFree")

DFS_MONTHS_clean <- DFS_MONTHS_clean[keep2]
DFS_STATUS_clean <- DFS_STATUS_clean[keep2]
brca.clean.df <- brca.clean.df[keep2, ]

# Build survival object
status <- ifelse(DFS_STATUS_clean == "1:Recurred/Progressed", 1, 0)
x <- as.matrix(brca.clean.df)
y <- Surv(time = DFS_MONTHS_clean, event = status)

# Fit Cox model with LASSO penalty (alpha = 1)
# Use parallel package to run it faster
n_cores <- parallel::detectCores() - 1
cl <- makeCluster(n_cores)
registerDoParallel(cl)

set.seed(123)
coxfit <- cv.glmnet(
  x, 
  y, 
  family = "cox",
  alpha = 1,              # LASSO
  nfolds = 5,             # 5-fold CV
  parallel = TRUE
)

stopCluster(cl)
registerDoSEQ()

# Best lambda
best_lambda <- coxfit$lambda.min

# Refit model at best lambda
coxfinal <- glmnet(x, 
                   y, 
                   family = "cox", 
                   alpha = 1, 
                   lambda = best_lambda)

# Get nonzero coefficients
cox_selected_genes <- rownames(coef(coxfinal))[coef(coxfinal)[,1] != 0]
length(cox_selected_genes)
## [1] 8
cox_selected_genes
## [1] "COL2A1"  "DIO1"    "SLC5A1"  "SEZ6L"   "PPP1R1A" "RET"     "SLC6A15"
## [8] "PCSK1"
# Predicted risk score
risk_scores <- predict(coxfinal, newx = x, type = "link")

cindex <- concordance.index(
  x = risk_scores, 
  surv.time = DFS_MONTHS_clean,
  surv.event = status
)

cindex$c.index
## [1] 0.6471709
# Visualize Kaplan-Meier curves
risk_group <- ifelse(risk_scores > median(risk_scores), "High", "Low")
df.km <- data.frame(
  DFS_MONTHS = DFS_MONTHS_clean,
  status = status,
  risk_group = risk_group
)
fit_km <- survfit(Surv(DFS_MONTHS, status) ~ risk_group, data = df.km)
ggsurvplot(fit_km, data = df.km, pval = TRUE, risk.table = TRUE, risk.table.height = 0.25)
